 EVALUATION PROCEDURES                                            6331 1451
                                                                  6331 1451
 Adopted procedures are based on careful theoretical analysis     6331 1451
 utilizing available experimental data, including optical model   6331 1451
 parameter search and nuclear reaction model calculations [Le02]. 6331 1451
                                                                  6331 1451
 OM parameter search was performed in one of two different        6331 1451
 ways:                                                            6331 1451
 - Interactive OM search code ABRXPL was used, based on the       6331 1451
   ABAREX code (spherical OM and Hauser-Feshbach with width       6331 1451
   fluctuation correction).                                       6331 1451
 - Parameters from the RIPL OM segment [Ri98], including CC OM    6331 1451
   for deformed nuclei, were used, to see whether any of the      6331 1451
   available parameter sets can be adopted.                       6331 1451
                                                                  6331 1451
 Nuclear reaction model calculations were performed with the      6331 1451
 code EMPIRE-II by M. Herman [He01, He02]. This is modularized    6331 1451
 statistical model code that integrates into a single system a    6331 1451
 number of important modules and features:                        6331 1451
                                                                  6331 1451
 - Spherical OM (code SCAT2 by O. Bersillone), and deformed OM    6331 1451
   including coupled-channels and DWBA (code ECIS95 by J.         6331 1451
   Raynal).                                                       6331 1451
 - Hauser-Feshbach statistical model including HRTW width         6331 1451
   fluctuation correction.                                        6331 1451
 - Qauntum-mechanical MSD TUL model (codes ORION & TRISTAN by     6331 1451
   H.Lenske), and MSC NVWY model.                                 6331 1451
 - Exciton model (code DEGAS by E. Betak). This code represents   6331 1451
   good approximation to DSD capture model.                       6331 1451
 - Complete gamma-ray cascade after emission of each particle,    6331 1451
   including realistic treatment of discrete transitions.         6331 1451
 - Access to OM segment of the RIPL library [Ri98].               6331 1451
 - Built-in input parameter files, such as masses, level density, 6331 1451
   discrete levels, OM parameters and gamma strength functions.   6331 1451
 - ENDF-6 formatting (utility code EMPEND by A. Trkov), coupled   6331 1451
   to grahpical presentation (utility code ZVView by V.Zerkin).   6331 1451
                                                                  6331 1451
                                                                  6331 1451
 PARAMETERIZATION                                                 6331 1451
                                                                  6331 1451
 Optical model                                                    6331 1451
 - ECIS95 code in the coupled-channels mode (CC) was used to      6331 1451
   calculate direct population of low-lying collective levels in  6331 1451
   the (n,n') channel:                                            6331 1451
    o CC OM parameters from the RIPL library (RIPL OM #2004),     6331 1451
      developed by Macklin and Young [Ma86] for 153-Eu, were      6331 1451
      adopted.                                                    6331 1451
    o The following levels of the g.s. rotational band in 153-Eu  6331 1451
      were coupled:                                               6331 1451
       0.0000 MeV   5/2+                                          6331 1451
       0.0834       7/2+                                          6331 1451
       0.1931       9/2+                                          6331 1451
      Quadrupole deformation parameter 0.300 was assumed.         6331 1451
    o Total, elastic, absorption and direct inelastic cross       6331 1451
      sections were taken from the CC calculations.               6331 1451
 - SCAT2 spherical OM code was used to calculate transmission     6331 1451
   coefficients for secondary neutrons, protons and alphas. The   6331 1451
   following OM parameterization was adopted:                     6331 1451
    o Neutrons - JAERI OM for 153-Eu (RIPL OM #221).              6331 1451
    o Protons - Becchetti-Greenless.                              6331 1451
    o Alpha particles - McFadden-Satchler.                        6331 1451
                                                                  6331 1451
 Level densities and discrete levels                              6331 1451
 - Gibert-Cameron level densities were used, as parameterized     6331 1451
   by the EMPIRE code, after careful matching to low-lying        6331 1451
   discrete levels.                                               6331 1451
 - Particle-hole level densities for preequilibrium component     6331 1451
   were set to g=A/13 for neutron channel, and g=A/17.5 for       6331 1451
   proton channel.                                                6331 1451
 - Discrete levels were taken from the built-in EMPIRE orsi.liv   6331 1451
   file that is based on the 1996 version of the ENSDF database.  6331 1451
                                                                  6331 1451
 Other parameters and tuning                                      6331 1451
 - Preequilibrium components were calculated using the following  6331 1451
   options:                                                       6331 1451
    o MSD and MSC models with default parameters for continuous   6331 1451
      portion of (n,n') channel.                                  6331 1451
    o Exciton model using the Kalbach parameter K=100 MeV-3 for   6331 1451
      (n,gamma) and (n,p) channels.                               6331 1451
 - EMPIRE default gamma-ray strength function was used for        6331 1451
   capture. This strength function was adjusted by about a factor 6331 1451
   of 1.5 to reproduce experimental capture data.                 6331 1451
